":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hey, \nMay I ask why such a low payout? This vulnerability could have caused the erasing of a lot of vine accounts, I think for example that it is much more severe than https://hackerone.com/reports/185862. Furthermore vine doesn't require email confirmation so I believe most of the accounts aren't confirmed and this vulnerability requires no user interaction, so I will be glad if you could explain.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-12-17T08:07:17.004Z","updated_at":"2016-12-17T08:07:17.004Z","actor":{"username":"mishre","cleared":false,"url":"/mishre","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"twitter","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1387646,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi @mishre,\nThis was determined to be a low severity bug and paid accordingly. The issue you reported only affects accounts that have not done email confirmation. Furthermore the account credentials can be reclaimed by the user with the email. Keeping those in mind we determined it was a low severity bug. \n\nAs for the report 185862, it exposed GPS information which is non public information, accordingly the reward was determined. \n\nThank you for helping keep Twitter secure!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-12-27T18:59:02.639Z","updated_at":"2016-12-27T18:59:02.639Z","actor":{"username":"rajat_tw","cleared":false,"url":"/rajat_tw","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"twitter","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1393367,"is_internal":false,"editable":false